# Task 3 Answers
#
# 1.
# list_tables + describe_table + run_select is safer than a single
# run_sql_query(sql) tool because the agent can discover the schema
# before writing SQL.
#
# Failure mode 1:
# The agent may guess a table name that does not exist.
#
# Failure mode 2:
# The agent may guess an incorrect column name and generate invalid SQL.
#
#
# 2.
# describe_table uses SQLAlchemy inspect() to read the schema live.
# This is better than documenting column names in the tool docstring
# because the schema can change over time and the tool will always
# return the current database structure.
#
#
# 3.
# Even with a SELECT-only guard, run_select can still be unsafe.
# A user may execute very expensive queries that scan huge tables.
#
# One way to harden the tool is:
# - limit returned rows
# - use query timeouts
# - use a read-only database role